TITLE: Students protest drag show planned for Catholic university Notre Dame
SUMMARY: Students at the University of Notre Dame are pushing back against a school-sponsored drag queen event scheduled for next month.

TITLE: Maine mass shooting suspect's family 'very cooperative' in manhunt that discovered his body: police
SUMMARY: The Maine state government held a press conference this weekend updating the public on mass-shooting suspect Robert Card, who was found dead of an apparent suicide in a box trailer.

TITLE: Hundreds of MIT alumni petition school to take campus threats against Jews 'seriously'
SUMMARY: Over 600 alumni, faculty and students of MIT are demanding the school take action after antisemitic chants rang out at an anti-Israel protest.

TITLE: Woman who married into Boston crime family revealed as Florida canal murder victim after vanishing: daughter
SUMMARY: Maehgan Smith got closure after Florida detectives approached her for a DNA sample. Her mother, Lori Kearsey, who disappeared in 1984, was finally identified.

TITLE: Elisa Lam's death at the notorious Cecil Hotel 'is no conspiracy,' former manager says: 'Very heartbreaking'
SUMMARY: Amy Price has written a new memoir, "Behind the Door: The Dark Truths and Untold Stories of the Cecil Hotel." She previously appeared in a Netflix true-crime docuseries.

TITLE: Maine mass shooting suspect Robert Card found dead with apparent self-inflicted gunshot wound
SUMMARY: Robert Card, the suspect in the Lewiston, Maine mass shooting, was found dead from an apparent self-inflicted gunshot wound, law enforcement confirmed.

TITLE: Maine plainclothes police officers were first to respond to mass shooting
SUMMARY: Maine Public Safety Commissioner Mike Sauschuck said that plainclothes police officers, who were training nearby, were the first to respond to Wednesday night's mass shooting at a bowling alley.

TITLE: Authorities seen with scuba gear in Maine river during manhunt for Robert Card
SUMMARY: Authorities on Friday were seen in scuba gear diving gear in Maine's Androscoggin River during the search for Robert Card, who's the primary suspect in Wednesday's Lewiston mass shooting.

TITLE: Victims of Maine mass shooting ranged in age from 14 to 76, medical examiner says
SUMMARY: The Maine Medical Examiner's office confirmed Friday that it has identified all 18 victims, saying the youngest was 14 years old and the oldest was 76.

TITLE: 3 sea turtles released into wild after rehabbing in Florida
SUMMARY: Three sea turtles have been released back into their natural habitats after being treated and rehabilitated at Florida's Clearwater Marine Aquarium.

TITLE: Inmate fatally stabbed at Tennessee courthouse while waiting to appear before judge
SUMMARY: Deion Byrd, 25, was fatally stabbed Thursday morning at a Memphis courthouse while awaiting an appearance before a judge. Fellow inmate Donnie Clay, 21, was charged in his death.

TITLE: Virgin Islands officials warn of lead, copper-contaminated water on St. Croix
SUMMARY: The U.S. Virgin Islands' government warned Friday against consumption of lead-and copper-contaminated tap water on the island of St. Croix.

TITLE: Murder suspect who escaped DC hospital captured after seven weeks on the run
SUMMARY: Accused killer Christopher Haynes was recaptured after nearly two months on the run. He escaped D.C. police with one wrist in a handcuff and a missing shoe last month.

TITLE: Tisch family members project faces of Israeli hostages on NYU building
SUMMARY: After posters of Israelis held hostage by Hamas were ripped down across NYU's campus, the Tisch family projected their images across the library on Monday.

TITLE: $6K reward offered for info on illegal black bear shooting in rural Louisiana
SUMMARY: A $6,000 reward is being offered for information leading to the arrest of whoever shot a black bear during closed season and abandoned the body near St. Francisville, Louisiana.

TITLE: Texan identified as pilot killed by small plane crash in eastern Wisconsin
SUMMARY: Steven Walker, 57, of Keller, Texas, has been identified as the pilot and sole victim in a small plane crash in Manitowoc County, Wisconsin.

TITLE: Tulane University condemns violence at dueling Palestinian, Israel protests: 'a dark day for our community'
SUMMARY: Protests on college campuses across the country have included a number of antisemitic incidents, and schools have struggled to keep the demonstrations peaceful.

TITLE: 3 teens shot, injured outside west Baltimore high school
SUMMARY: Three teenagers were shot and injured outside a high school in west Baltimore as classes started Friday morning, according to officials.

TITLE: Coast Guard abandons search for missing fishermen off Georgia coast
SUMMARY: The Coast Guard has abandoned its search for the fishing vessel Carol Ann, last seen setting sail off the Georgia coast nearly two weeks ago.

TITLE: Minnesota gun owner charged after girlfriend's son, 4, fatally shoots younger brother
SUMMARY: Colton Mammenga, 33, of Welcome, Minnesota, faces manslaughter and child endangerment charges after his girlfriend's four-year-old son fatally shot his two-year-old brother.

TITLE: Special ed teacher accused of trying to meet up with teen boy for sex
SUMMARY: A Missouri high school teacher was arrested last week on allegations she sent explicit videos to a teen student and tried to proposition him for sex, according to court records.

TITLE: Man faces murder charge connected to death of Philadelphia journalist
SUMMARY: A murder charge has been filed against a 19-year-old in connection to the death of a Pennsylvania journalist who was fatally shot in his home in early October.

TITLE: Indiana police officer fatally shoots trespassing suspect inside Burger King
SUMMARY: An Indiana police officer shot and killed a trespassing suspect following a physical altercation inside an Indianapolis Burger King on Thursday evening.

TITLE: Maine shooting investigators to deploy divers to search river, confirm suspect left 'note'
SUMMARY: Divers are searching a boat launch area Friday in Lisbon, Maine, in the manhunt for Lewiston mass shootings suspect Robert Card, officials say.

TITLE: Robert Card manhunt: Experts weigh Maine mass murder suspectâ€™s potential escape routes
SUMMARY: Experts weigh in on the potential escape routes of Robert Card, who is suspected of killing 18 people and injuring 13 others in a mass shooting in Maine.
